<br>
1.  Go to a LOT of fear raids before you even think about leading your own.  <br>
2.  Be prepared to do a fear raid KNOWING that you have a good chance of getting wiped out on the break.  <br>
3.  Be prepared to die.  Be prepared to have unrezzable corpses from the break.    <br>
4.  Aggro radius is HUGE.  Thing will aggro on you from outside spell casting range, bring a lot of friends, and get you killed.<br>
5.  Almost all mobs have have the ability to randomly see invis.  (While one scarleling doesn't see invis, others scarelings CAN.)<br>
6.  Scarelings are $*^%.  They have the ability to teleport people across the zone like a shadowstep.  You'll be trying to stay against a zone wall during break to avoid roamers, and they'll port you right out in the middle of them.  <br>
7.  There are no safespots.  In hate, you can have everyone wipe, then rezz them in at the ss.  In fear,  if you try to rezz someone in, they get aggro from across the zone and get killed.<br>
8.  The raid MUST be well organized by people that have done fear MANY times.  Raiders must know what they are doing, where to go, etc.  <br>
<br>
Plane of fear is a zone with rules completely different to most other zones in the game.  The best way for you to learn it is to personally go there and see for yourself.<br>
<br>
